names(commune)
##  [1] "ID"         "STATUT"     "INSEE_COM"  "NOM_COM"    "INSEE_ARR"

3.2 D√©placement manuel

Id√©e : on cpt le nb de pts, puis on les envoie √† un √©cart si > 2 L‚Äô√©cart est d√©pendant de l‚Äô√©chelle r√©gionale

nrow(data5)
## [1] 5
pt <- data5$geometry[1]
ecart <- 10000 * 0.7
plot (region$geom [11,], bg = "antiquewhite1")
plot(pt , add = TRUE)
plot( pt + c(ecart,0), col= "red", add = TRUE )
plot( pt- c(ecart,0), col= "red", add = TRUE)
plot(pt - c(ecart, ecart), add = TRUE)
plot( pt + c(0, ecart)  ,col = "green", add = T)
plot( pt - c(0, ecart)  ,col = "green", add = T)
plot(data, pch = 19, col = "black", add = TRUE)
